  "explanation": "## Arsenic Green Fluorescence Biosensor\n**Pattern:** Biosensor\n**Organism:** Escherichia coli\n\n### Description\nBiosensor that detects arsenic and produces green fluorescence\n\n### Transcription Units\n- **sensor**: Pars Arsenic Sensing Promoter -> RBS B0034 -> ArsR Transcription Factor -> Double Terminator B0015 (452 bp)\n- **reporter**: GFP (Green Fluorescent Protein) (717 bp)\n\n### Regulatory Connections\n- sensor --[activates]--> regulator\n- regulator --[activates]--> reporter\n\n### Component Details\n- **sensor** (promoter): Pars Arsenic Sensing Promoter -- Promoter responsive to arsenite ions, repressed by ArsR in the absence of arsenic\n- **regulator** (regulator): ArsR Transcription Factor -- Arsenic-responsive transcriptional repressor. Dissociates from Pars in the presence of arsenite.\n- **reporter** (reporter): GFP (Green Fluorescent Protein) -- Green fluorescent protein. Emits at 509 nm.\n\n**Total construct:** ~1169 bp across 2 transcription unit(s)",
